  "issue_title": "`gin.Error` doesn't implement `Unwrap` method for non-pointers",
  "issue_body": "I expect following code to print the wrapped error in both pointer and non-pointer uses. But it prints nil when you use it without pointer\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"errors\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n)\n\nfunc main() {\n\terr := gin.Error{Err: errors.New(\"test error\")}\n\tfmt.Println(errors.Unwrap(err))  // prints nil\n\tfmt.Println(errors.Unwrap(&err)) // prints \"test error\" correctly\n}\n```\n\nhttps://github.com/gin-gonic/gin/pull/631 removed pointer from `Error()` receiver to make `gin.Error` usable without pointer but the same change needs to be done for `Unwrap()` method as well",
  "merged_at": "2025-05-11T14:38:33Z",
